          • [ - ] Papichulo - member since 13-Jul-13

            Getting better. But the sooner Barca step away from tiki taka, the better. Practically none of their goals as of late have come from any kind of last possession, rather, they came from quick direct attacks, counter attacks or set pieces. And once the plan ceases being get the ball to Messi, also will be much better. Don't get me wrong, Messi is amazing, but he can't out dribble 4 defenders every time. They switch things up, they can take la liga - they don't they become to predictable, opposition will just park the bus - worst still, currently Barca are letting teams have the time to set up their bus just perfectly. Hopefully a new year will bring an improvement on style.
